HEADWORD: Elation
<hw>E*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>elatio</ets>. See <er>Elate</er>.]</ety> <def>A lifting up by
success; exaltation; inflation with pride of prosperity.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Felt the <xex>elation</xex> of triumph.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

